result.name: Noodle Joy

reviews.text:
I walked pass Noodle Joy a few times before and was always attracted by its nice LED sign. It seems that Noodle Joy is run by a few Taiwanese people, all the staff are very polite and friendly, which gives me a very welcoming feeling and makes my dining experience really enjoyable.

To start with, I tried out their signature Minced Pork Rice. Some say that if you wanna see if a Taiwanese restaurant is good, try their minced pork rice. I guess Noodle Joy is a good one in this case, as the minced pork rice they make is really gorgeous. The fat in the minced pork is right to the point, and the amount of sauce is just right to mix well with the rice and meat. The rice is kinda like Japanese rice, which is rounder and delicious.

I also got a Taiwanese bun. It’s made fresh upon ordering, so it did take a bit of time for preparation. The bread is so fluffy! Love it! And the pork belly inside is super delicious indeed! Another must try of Noodle Joy!

Fast casual restaurant that serves Taiwanese food. If you are expecting the food to be comparable to Taipei then you will likely be disappointed. However, if your expectation is a tasty meal at a reasonable price then you will like this place.  

The beef noodle soup is one of the Bette ones I have had in Hong Kong. The noodles are cooked nicely and the soup has a nice depth of flavor. The meat could be more tender but that really is my only complaint. The dumplings here are also quite good and I would recommend ordering that as well. The Taiwanese sausage was a bit dry and I wouldn’t recommend ordering. The lou rou fan here is also pretty decent.
Nice atmosphere but everything we ordered was supremely bland if not below average.  Beef noodle was flavorless, fried chicken was passable... Side dishes passable... No reason to go back...
Loved the dumplings and the jasmine tea was amazing (and I ain’t no tea drinker). Will be back daily or more often if time allows

Nice retro decors all around and that was all there is.  Staffs looked like they didnt want to be there, the guy at the check out looked like he wanted to stab someone. My $60 beef slices consisted of literally 4 slices of chewy beef in a bowl of flavouring.  They might as well have robbed me, as the overall experience would have been similar.
